(185, 'Mohamad Qatu', 'Team Watta-Box', ''),
(186, 'Mohamad Qatu', 'Riverboat Clinic', ''),
(187, 'Sufian Qrunfleh', 'Portable Air Filtration Device', 'This is a fantastic idea! I love it!\r\nDo you think you can have this device work using a battery charge instead of plugged in?\r\nEspecially for the portable device. Thank you!'),
(188, 'Sufian Qrunfleh', 'AI Music Tracker', 'Great idea! You guys are awesome!\r\nWhen you speak softly, you said the app doesn\'t register the voice. Have you guys thought about a microphone and then connect it to your iPhone or the device you installed the app in? Maybe that will help in catching the words. '),
(189, 'Sufian Qrunfleh', 'Riverboat Clinic', 'Great idea! I like it!\r\nMy only concern is how would you transfer patients from the isolated area to this clinic boat? Have you thought about maybe flying a helicopter to transfer the patients to the boat?\r\n '),
(190, 'Sufian Qrunfleh', 'Rainwater Energy Generation', 'Fantastic idea! For the storage tank, do you think we can implement this idea on every house and use the storage water to pump back to consume it  ( pump it back right away after filtering it)?'),
(191, 'Sufian Qrunfleh', 'The Cable Connector', 'Great idea! I see the porotype is made of cardboard. Have you thought about the actual material when you launch your  product :) Do you think plastic will hold and secure the connection?\r\n'),
(192, 'Andrew Monticello', 'Toby Wright & Efe Akinci', 'In your video pitch avoid using the word \"So\".  The pitch seemed well rehearsed but left the viewer with many questions.  If control is a key incentive to using a car how does making an autonomous vehicle satisfy that incentive?  Were things like weather, balancing of the bicycle, and battery range considered?  When stating a fact from a study that study should be specifically called out instead of saying \"A study found\".\r\nLog book is needed to properly evaluate the invention.'),
(193, 'Susan Miller', 'Skellies', 'Very nice presentation! Here are some tips for taking your product to the next step. When identifying the Market Potential, gather some statistics. How many people who wear glasses are having this problem with masks fogging up? You can put together a quick survey and send it out to get some quantitative data. \r\nAnother thing to consider is the social value of your product. You gave us some positive impacts (more people may wear masks), but are there any negative impacts? '),
(194, 'Andrew Monticello', 'ID Pen', 'The online pitch seemed like the presenters were reading off of a cue card and did not rehearse well enough.  The speech was too fast and rushed, with too much content for a pitch.  The design alternatives were very similar and did not address the overall problem statement of document fraud.  It would have been better to identify two different solutions and settle on the pen.\r\nTesting did not result in product improvement, or suggestions for product improvement.\r\nMarket study did not address that this invention would require people to carry an additional form of verification and could be seen as an inconvenience. '),
(195, 'Susan Miller', 'Team Crank', 'This is a very cool idea. Here are my questions for your team.\r\n\r\nDo you have a Log Book? I am only seeing a picture of your product in the Log Book section and can only judge based off of that and your video pitch.\r\n\r\nWhat is targeted market - who are you trying to sell this product to? Is it just iPhone users? \r\n\r\nWhat is the market potential for this? How many people are having this issue and would buy your product? I suggest creating a quick market survey to get some quantitative data.\r\n'),
(196, 'Andrew Monticello', 'AI Music Tracker', 'In video pitch avoid using words \"Um, uh, like, stuff\".  Avoid specifically calling out ownership or work provided. \"I have to\", or \"we ending up choosing Isaac\'s design.\"\r\nThe app has a limited usefulness to just vocal recognition but does not address the instrumentation part of making music.  The other referenced apps and websites also include chords or chord progressions.  The goal  does not incorporate the entirety of music, instead focusing on a vocal tracker.\r\nCosts do not align between sections.  In the product outcome section the app is stated to be free, while in the Cost section a price and service fee are identified. Even a \"free\" app needs to provide a revenue source for backend support.  Time to develop the app is not free, but this could be stated in hours of work required.\r\nPay attention to the log book formatting, make sure answers line up to questions when using column formatting.  Avoid splitting up sections between multiple pages.\r\nIndividual contributions do not need to be identified.  Avoid statements with the word I, unless specifically asked.'),
(197, 'Susan Miller', 'Walking Shipping Container Home', 'This is a really unique idea! Great job with your presentation and log book.\r\n\r\nYou identified some great positive impacts that your product might have for social values. Can you think of any negative impacts that it might have as well? '),
(198, 'Susan Miller', 'W-Arm', 'This is a very interesting concept! I have a few questions for you.\r\n\r\nHow many people are having this problem and would be interested in your solution? \r\n\r\nYou listed some great positive impacts that your product might provide. Can you think of some negative impacts as well? '),
(199, 'Susan Miller', 'The Distance Detector ', '														'),
(201, 'Steve Rohde', 'ID Pen', 'Why not just a fingerprint scanner on the phone?'),
(202, 'Steve Rohde', 'Ice Tray', ''),
(203, 'Steve Rohde', 'FruitFresh', 'How big does device need to be?\r\nCost?'),
(204, 'Emma Barnes', 'ID Pen', ''),
(205, 'Emma Barnes', '2 in 1 Mask', ''),
(206, 'Courtney Dunbar', 'Automatic kelp elevator', 'Hi guys. I really enjoyed your invention. I liked that you are very persistent to save our struggling planet, and you chose something I have never even thought of before. Most people go for usual oil spill cleanup inventions, or garbage clean up inventions which are already out there. But you\'re growing kelp?! Wow! Very cool and neat idea. I just want to say your pitch did feel a little rushed, and you seemed nervous. Don\'t be nervous- you have a pretty cool invention! Slow down, relax and really grab your audiences attentions. If I can make a suggestion, start your pitch off with a hook. Maybe a question or a scenario to really grab your audience\'s attention! I do have one question, will the kelp still adequately grow if there is an overwhelming amount of garbage in the ocean in that area? I was also curious as to why you chose the Pacific Northwest to place the device. I think it\'s a good idea, because the water there stays about the same temperature year around, but also consider things like tsunamis when plotting where to put the device! Overall, an interesting and cool invention. Good luck!'),
(207, 'Courtney Dunbar', 'BeatRunner', 'Hi guys! I really enjoyed listening to your invention idea. I completely agree that music motivates people because when I run at the gym, if I put my music on shuffle and a slow song comes on, I\'m mad because it immediately kills my vibe. I think this is definitely something that could be marketed. I want to also say to start of your pitch by selling the audience. Ask an attention grabbing question or scenario to really capture the audience\'s attention. Overall, nicely done and I can see this being something in the future to have. Good luck!'),
(208, 'Courtney Dunbar', 'Auto Door Sanitizer', 'Hi guys! This was such a cool invention to read about! I think this is very useful and very important to have especially during flu and COVID seasons. It\'s honestly just crucial to have at all times of the year. I think the only questions I have are: How often would it need to be refilled with sanitizing chemicals? And how long would the adhesive last? Other than that, a job well done. Very interesting invention and I hope we have something like this in the future!'),
(209, 'Courtney Dunbar', 'Virtual Assimilation', 'Hello! Wow I am absolutely blown away by the amount of work you put into this! A job well done, definitely. I really like this invention a lot because I suffer from motion sickness myself so this definitely hit home for me. I\'ve always had interest in trying out VR, although I could never do it long because I would probably puke from the dizziness. Your invention would help a lot of people just like me! Despite all the positives, I had to give you half credit on your video pitch because it was a bad link. I know that\'s not something you can control, but maybe post it on Youtube using a public account/viewing. It told me I was forbidden to access the video. Either way, I know you submitted one so it would be unfair to give you a 0/15 on it, so I gave you half credit. This is an awesome invention. Good luck! '),
(210, 'Courtney Dunbar', 'Blue Light Eye Protection', 'Hello! I really liked your idea and thought it was pretty important especially in today\'s time where everyone and anyone is on their phones and computers because we are faced with a global pandemic. I also want to say that your video pitch was the only pitch I\'ve seen that actually made me smile and laugh! I was looking for this aspect in all of the presentations, but yours was the only one that did it for me! I also wanted to say that I liked that you actually hand made a prototype and I could even see it at use! That being said, I did have to score you a 0 on logbook because you do not have one, and also there\'s not much information on different trials and errors during your invention process. I think you should add more details on different trials, add a logbook, and you also need resources to provide support for your invention. Good luck!'),
(211, 'Amy Johnson', 'BeatRunner', 'Nice job! I would definitely use this product if you were able to expand it to include matching music to strokes per minute for a rowing machine. I don\'t think it would be too difficult to modify as you could still likely use the foot pressure sensor to measure when one pushes off to initiate the stroke.\r\nWhile the logbook is for your team, I would keep in mind that it is not *just* for your team. It would be helpful to have more detailed explanation for how you filled out the decision matrix, for example. You may also want to consider eliminating abbreviations (e.g., idk) and more conversational terms and spellings (e.g., random people, lil).\r\nIf you move on to the next round and have a chance to re-record your pitch, I would recommend 1) not having a ceiling fan in the recording frame and 2) changing the color scheme on the slide with the example of the coding as it was very difficult to read. \r\nIt would also be great to include the coding in the log book, as well as the questions and answers you received from your survey of potential users.'),
(212, 'Amy Johnson', 'The Dream Team', 'This is a really cool idea, I just wish I knew more about it. You only used about half of your allotted pitch time, so you had the opportunity to explain more of the process of your feeder\'s design and its features. For example, how does the power cord feed through the tiny hole in the bottom of the feeder? Does it detach from the heating pad or is the hole shown not to scale?\r\n\r\nWhile the logbook is for your team, I would keep in mind that it is not *just* for your team. Here is where you could have included potential user survey questions and responses as well as a more detailed narrative about how the project progressed over time. Also, you may want to reread it to consider if everything in there is something you would want a judge to read. You spent a lot of space in your logbook on the marketing of the product, but very little on the product itself. It may be beneficial to shift your efforts to more closely fit the requirements of the project. '),
(213, 'Amy Johnson', 'Kloehn & Chadha', 'Handy idea! I can definitely see how this would be useful to someone who spends a lot of time in a vehicle. I do wish I understood more about the refinement process for the design. You do a nice job of describing what changes in the design occur, but it is not clear to me why those changes were made. The drawings a helpful, but really tiny in the video viewer so it is hard to make out the details. You had time extra left for your video, so you could have included fewer images per slide in order to make them larger and easier to view. Including a log book would also have made it easier to include more and larger images as well as more details about the project.\r\nSome things I wondered about: Will this fit into different sized cup holders (some are larger than others)? How does the top rubber part accommodate different shaped and sized sauce cups? It looks to be one continuous piece. Also, how does the top fit on to keep spills from happening? How much will this cost to manufacture?'),
(214, 'Amy Johnson', 'Walking Shipping Container Home', 'Such a very cool idea!\r\nIf you are to move to the next round of competition and have the opportunity to re-record your pitch, I\'d consider 1) having the slides take up more of the screen so the information on the slides is a bit larger and easier to see and 2) either not sit in a chair that swivels or be mindful of not swiveling during the presentation.\r\n\r\nI wondered about the cost of moving a home in the more traditional way. You may have had that on one of the slides but I couldn\'t clearly read it and I don\'t recall you talking about it. Also, do you have a sense of how much this system you\'ve designed will cost? Can the system be used separately from the shipping container home if someone liked the idea but wanted a home constructed from wood, let\'s say, or must they be used together? Did you do any potential user surveys? It would be great to include the questions and responses in your log book.\r\nKeep up the good work!'),
(215, 'Amy Johnson', 'Blue Light Eye Protection', 'I completely understand the need for this product, but I wish I knew more about it. Many aspects of the required information are missing. You had a lot of time left for the video, so there was the opportunity to include more information. The log book was also missing, which was another avenue for reporting on the process of the project.\r\nIt feels like an updated version of the old \"blue blocker\" glasses. It would be great to know how these are different. How much would they cost? Did you do any potential user surveys (beyond the guy in the video)? If so, what were the questions and the responses?'),
(216, 'Heidi Daugherty', 'Portable Air Filtration Device', ''),
(217, 'Heidi Daugherty', 'Indoor Eating Bubble', ''),
(218, 'Heidi Daugherty', 'Auto Door Sanitizer', ''),
(219, 'Heidi Daugherty', 'Kloehn & Chadha', ''),
(220, 'Raouf Abbas', 'Toby Wright & Efe Akinci', 'Great Project! The Idea is very Interesting and has a lot of potential. \r\nQ: How did you come to this Idea? how was your journey during your designing process. was this your first Idea?  \r\nyour presentation was very well done! I think it would have been more informative if you had some visuals to aid your explanations.  \r\n\r\n'),
(221, 'Marie Jaster', 'Portable Air Filtration Device', 'I think this is a great invention! My only question is lets say somebody wants to use to clean a bigger space, would they buy multiple devices or would it not be as effective? Also how can we trust that it is effectively cleaning the air? Great job!!!'),
(222, 'Marie Jaster', 'BeatRunner', 'I think this idea is super awesome:) One question  I have is what do you expect the life expectancy to be for this device? How long will it last before you need to get a new one?'),
(223, 'Marie Jaster', 'Riverboat Clinic', 'Super cool idea! A question I have is would this have any negative effects on our environment or the water system? And another thing I was wondering is how much would this all cost to build ?'),
(224, 'Marie Jaster', 'Ice Tray', 'Hey good job! How do you know that this would solve the problem for overheating computers? Do you think there should be a solution that is put inside the computer itself rather than on the outside? '),
(225, 'Marie Jaster', 'Rainwater Energy Generation', 'Hey Cali! I really enjoyed your pitch and think you idea is super cool:) I know you mentioned that this would have to be used probably in warmer climates but how much of the population that needs clean water and electricity, lives in climates that are cooler or drier and could we somehow use this invention to help them too?'),
(226, 'Raouf Abbas', 'Smart Face Shield', 'This Idea is Very Interesting and very helpful especially right now during this pandemic.'),
(227, 'Raouf Abbas', 'Search and Rescue Drone Universal Attachment System (SDUAS)', ''),
(228, 'Andrew Monticello', 'Smart Face Shield', 'Good evaluation of sources, but should also have considered cell  phone sanitization products that do not involve washing, or similar products like Google Glass.  An opportunity exists to improve on the negative response of Google Glass .  Clever alternative to the cell phone screen.  A HUD projector may allow the shield to be replaced with minimal expense.\r\nPresentation material was well understood but speech could have use more practice.  Room to improve presentation by not having to move video image.'),
(229, 'Andrew Monticello', 'Virtual Assimilation', 'Only one source plus personal story for problem statement.  It would have been better to have some interface.  If the original coding source was not available there are many sources to design the top level application without the backend.  Value proposition and market value were not clearly identified.\r\nVideo pitch was not available.'),
(230, 'Marissa Moore', 'Skellies', 'This invention was a really good idea! I know a lot of friends and family who would definitely use one of your masks to prevent their glasses from fogging up! I like how you mentioned that this product could also help ensure people are wearing their masks correctly because their glasses fogging up would no longer pose an issue! '),
(231, 'Marissa Moore', 'Team Crank', 'This was a good idea for people who constantly need to be charging their iPhones! I liked how you thought of a way to make a portable charger that doesn\'t need to charge and won\'t die soon after you start using it! One thing to improve on in the future is your logbook, the only thing that was included under your logbook link was a single picture of your invention! I would have loved to look at your diagrams, research, and overall process while watching your video and learning about your product! '),
(232, 'Marissa Moore', 'Smart Face Shield', 'Your product was such a unique and useful idea! Phones are so gross and collect so many germs, it would be really useful and practical to invest in your invention! Your research, video, and logbook were all very interesting and I enjoyed imagining the benefits of using your product on my trips to the grocery store! '),
(233, 'Marissa Moore', 'Walking Shipping Container Home', 'Your invention was so complex and unique! This idea had never crossed my mind, but I bet this would be especially helpful in areas that are susceptible to hurricanes! I would have like to seen more about the market viability as well as the environmental and societal effects! Great invention and engineering in designing this product!'),
(234, 'Marissa Moore', 'FruitFresh', 'This would definitely be a product that I would buy! I feel like my fresh produce always goes bad, so it was really neat seeing your research in creating a container that helps you keep your fruit fresh and eat/enjoy it at the best time! I love the detail and research that went into designing this invention! '),
(235, 'Tareq Khan', 'Rainwater Energy Generation', 'Interesting idea and good presentation! The power generated from this approach might not enough for powering the 110 V AC home appliances - try to think about how to increase the output voltage and power. You may also use the vibration of rain falling to generate electricity using a piezoelectric element.\r\n\r\n'),
(236, 'Tareq Khan', 'W-Arm', 'Opening and closing windows automatically based on outside and inside temperature is a nice idea! You need to think critically does this approach solves the AC cooling and pollution problem, because opening the window might not be enough to cool the room on a hot summer day. You may think of a fan that will blow air over ice or something like that.'),
(237, 'Tareq Khan', 'The Distance Detector ', 'Nice idea and well done! Next job is to program an Arduino, interface the sensor and the warning light.  '),
(238, 'Tareq Khan', 'Search and Rescue Drone Universal Attachment System (SDUAS)', 'Well done. You need to check with different cameras and verify whether your design is an easy-to-use universal solution.  '),
(239, 'Tareq Khan', '3D Printing Filament Recycling System', 'Interesting idea! Write using clear and short sentences. During oral presentation, make sure the sound is clear and you are showing enthusiasm. '),
(240, 'Emma Barnes', 'Ice Tray', 'The video doesn\'t mention anything about the fan, and I don\'t see it on the final product, was that idea scrapped?'),
(241, 'Emma Barnes', 'FruitFresh', ''),
(242, 'Emma Barnes', '3D Printing Filament Recycling System', 'Presentation lacks energy'),
(243, 'Raouf Abbas', 'Virtual Assimilation', ''),
(244, 'Dan ', 'Indoor Eating Bubble', 'Could you go into more details about the capabilities of the UV light, filters and other mechanical air movement devices?  This might convince me that your product scientifically works.'),
(245, 'Dan ', 'Kloehn & Chadha', 'Is this device encouraging distracted driving by encouraging eating behind the wheel, or does it reduce distracted driving by making sauce locations fixed and more stable?\r\nCould you have done more testing before the final prototype was made to show your invention in use? Explain what you would do?'),
(246, 'Dan ', 'Team Watta-Box', 'Would using aluminum instead of plastic really make the product more recyclable?  Can a metal box vs. a plastic box do more scratching and nick-damage to boats made of coated fiberglass?  Great pitch video.  Excelled prototype.  Could you have done more testing and refining? (i.e., put an adhesive closed cell foam on the bottom of the container to make it float better and do less scratching?'),
(247, 'Dan ', 'Toilet Plunger', 'he social impact was well described on the sanitation side.  But what is the cost to maintain the complexity of the system?  \r\nYou clearly described the design of the product.  But you did not give any cost to build information and possible selling price - what is the premium over a toiletus regularis? (Latin/Greek?)'),
(248, 'Dan ', 'The Cable Connector', 'After reviewing the logbook I can see the magnitude of the USB C cable problems.  Why did I not see any examples for guitars? This made my understanding the  presentation a bit vague.\r\nCan you describe why there were four suction cups?'),
