(0, 205, 'Achievement - Announcements (Mr Anjum, Mr Khusro or anyone else can make these announcement)\r\n1)	Past and current NED SCHOLARS activities\r\na.	Scholarships â€“ In 2017 we awarded 50 scholarships\r\nb.	Mentorship â€“ There are 15 active mentors working with all our scholarship holders\r\nc.	Internships â€“ 19 were awarded in 2017; in PIA, Thar Coal, \r\nd.	Webinar /training â€“ Soft skills, AutoCAD = April 2017; In August there will be certification training on Six Sigma (yellow belt) and workshops on Communication and speech anxiety. These are help in collaboration with NED Directorate of Industry Liaison (DIL) office; thank you Prof Ali Zulqarnain in helping us out in scheduling and other arrangements.\r\n ', 'b.	In 2016 Annual NED Alumni convention was held in Houston, TEXAS. The theme of the convention was \"Nurturing Our Alma Mater\". Dr. Muhammad Afzal Haque, Ex NED Vice Chancellor, attended the convention and discuss the needs of NED university and roles/ways Alumni Association can play in its continued development. Mr Javaid Iqbal, president of NED Alumni Association of TEXAS, & Mr Afzaal, 2016 conventionâ€™s chairperson also contacted Dr. Sarosh H. Lodhi when he became new Vice Chancellor, in which the VC identified several projects through which the alumni of North America can make a positive contribution to NED. During this 2016 Annual NED Alumni convention held in Houston a sum of about Rs 2000000 (Twenty laks) was collected by NED Alumni Association of TEXAS. ', '1)	How can NED SCHOLARS help NED in their upcoming century celebration? Is there any committee that NED University has created to plan for this activity?\r\n2)	Can students who are getting our scholarship, be able to take courses at NED Summer university at a discounted rate? NED Scholars can upfront buy x number of seats in any such summer courses and let our scholarship holders attend it free. Is it possible that we get some discount from NED Summer courses?\r\n', '1)	NED Scholars - Laptop distribution\r\na.	Sameena Jamshaid\r\nb.	Maria Aslam Pervaiz\r\nc.	Muhammad Rafay\r\nd.	Muhammad Umar \r\ne.	Shahida Parveen \r\n', '2021-06-28 07:36:22'),
