(331, 229, '<p><strong>Piping, Pressure Washers, Sump Pump, Gear Rack, Motor with gear, sheet metal, Sheet metal with holes, Laser Sensor, 2 motors to make it&nbsp; the whole thing rol.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>All together they would cost about 1700 dollars.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n ', '<p>I will get my parts at home appliance stores and if I cant find them there I will search for them online.&nbsp;</p>\r\n ', '<p>I will need to understand how water pumps work and how to set up a water system. I will also need to understand how hydraulic pumps work because half of the invention will be below the ground.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>The people who can help me are my parents and my mentors. My mentors will help a lot since if I need to I can use the labs at emu.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2022-02-19 06:20:42'),
(319, 228, '<p><strong>Here is a list of parts, materials, and tools I will need to build my invention</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Item/Part</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Function/Purpose</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>9v/12-volt batteries</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Power the relay switch and solenoids</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Syringes</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Fill tube</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>plastic sealer</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Seal tube</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Raspberry Pi</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Process information from camera and send to Book2Braille machine</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>12V 4mm Stroke Mini DC Solenoid Electromagnet&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>compress tubes</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>12mm Piezo Elements Sounder Sensor Trigger Drum Disc+Wire Copper</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>toggle between different characters</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Adafruit Flex Cable for Raspberry Pi Camera&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Give extra length to the camera cord</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>5V 8 Channel Relay Module Board for Arduino PIC AVR DSP ARM</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Give separate signals to each solenoid</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Camera for Raspberry Pi</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>scan characters on document</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Materials used per cell:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LDPE &mdash; 2, 165.1 mm x 139.7mm sheets (6.5&rdquo; x 5.5&rdquo;)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cost: $0.01&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>30 gauge copper wire&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cost: $4.56</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>8 neodymium magnets</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cost: $0.05</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Thin acrylic:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cost: $3</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Single-use materials:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2, 9v batteries:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cost: $4.97</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>8 channel relay:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cost: $5.50</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Raspberry pi &mdash; $10</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ArduCam &mdash; $10</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Total for 10 cells: 10 * (0.01 + 4.56 + 0.01 + 1) + 4.97 + 5.50 + 10 + 10 = $86.31</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Equation: cost = 6.01(x) + 30.47 (where x is number of cells)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n ', '<p><strong>&nbsp;I plan to purchase the parts and materials from Amazon. I think a few items are also available at other retailers such as Walmart or eBay.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n ', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>How does a solenoid work</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>How to build an actuator</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>How to wire a Raspberry Pi&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>How to write a program in python that can recognize and display text in a book</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p><strong>I tried to build the prototype on my own with help from online tutorials and youtube videos. My mentors professor&nbsp;Shiri Vivek&nbsp;of Eastern Michigan University were very helpful in providing suggestions, ideas, and feedback throughout the process.</strong></p>\r\n', '2022-02-19 07:12:27'),
(331, 229, '<p><strong>Piping 50$, Pressure Washers 150*5$ 750, Sump Pump 200$, Gear Rack 20$, Motor with gear 50$, sheet metal 10*15 150, Sheet metal with holes 50*5$ 250, Laser Sensor 30$, and 2 motors to make it&nbsp; the whole thing roll.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The whole thing would cose around 1700$.</p>\r\n ', '<p><br />\r\nI will get my parts at home appliance stores and if I cant find them there I will search for them online.</p>\r\n ', '<p>I will need to understand how water pumps work and how to set up a water system. I will also need to understand how hydraulic pumps work because half of the invention will be below the ground.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>The people who can help me are my parents and my mentors. My mentors will help a lot since if I need to I can use the labs at emu.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2022-02-20 03:24:55'),
