(332, 231, 0x32303232303131385f313835313237202831292e6a7067, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/H4z4smFusE-Qi7r2zVRTnvo2478jEs7zYDLR-1yNvMLuDObsB1q-jsvuh8Xwck1fKiOI_2L3BNWOlKjIlpWXyD7bGe-1P3sQDutTgElNdF8Hx2FXeN5_C_oTlB8o1G-FgA\" style=\"height:225px; width:300px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; How it works</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The reflector will reflect sunlight onto the coper tubing the copper tubing will then heat up and heat the water inside the copper tubing, this will distribute the heat evenly across the pot when cooking.</p>\r\n ', '2022-02-18 03:57:40'),
(331, 229, '', '<p>This machine has a 4 step process. The first thing that the user does is throw everything they have into the machine but do not throw in plastic bags. After that, step one(prototype 1) starts happening. Step one is where all the stuff you have thrown into will be sorted into two groups. Group one is plastic, metal, and glass i.e. the recyclables, and group two is anything else. Each step will be explained in detail after this paragraph. Step two(prototype 2) is when everything in group 1 is sent to a washer that will clean it. After everything is cleaned it moves on to step 3 which is it gets sorted again. This time it sorts metal, plastic, and glass into separate groups. Each of these groups except glass will be sent to step 4. The glass will be sent to a normal trash can. The plastics and the metals will be sent to step 4 which is a compactor that will compact all the plastics and the metals until they are emptied.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prototype 1 will first allow 2-3 pieces of trash to be lowered onto a conveyor belt. On the conveyor belt, there will be a camera using R-FCN(Region-based Fully Convolutional Network) which is an object recognition algorithm to sense what the trash is. For this stage, it will sort between group 1(plastic, glass, metal) and everything else but it will use a 40% match rate to sort instead of the default 95%. This stage is mainly done to reduce the amount of trash getting into the washer. So a 40% match rate is done because object recognition software struggles to identify the object unless it is clean. So a 40% match rate will allow it to reduce the amount of trash in the cleaner and still have all of group 1 be sent to the washer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prototype 2 will have all of group 2(plastic, metal, glass) filling up inside it until it reaches 50% capacity. After that happens the cleaning cycle starts. The cycle starts with the 5 power washers spraying the plastic. They will have 4 on each side of the container and 1 on the top of the container. The pressure washers are all 500 psi and will be one for one minute. After one minute the inner container will spin for 30 seconds. This is done to dry the plastic as much as possible. After the spin is done then the bottom of the container will open and allow all the plastics to go.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prototype 3 sorts group one into three separate groups which are plastic, glass, and metal. The sorting is done in the same format as step 1 but this time it is sorted between glass, metal, and glass. After this is done glass is sent to its trash can while metal and plastic are sent to step 4.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 4 is another cleaner. It works exactly the same as step 2 after that metal and plastic are sent to step 4. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 4 is a compactor. The compactor starts to compact after it reaches 75% capacity. After that happens it starts crushing the metal and the plastic from the top. This is done to reduce the number of times the trashman has to pick it up. If even after it is compacted and it&#39;s at 90% capacity then they will let the pickup crew know to come and get it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This machine will be half underground to reduce the amount it intrudes above the ground. It will be lifted up using a hydraulic lift because of the weight of the machine.&nbsp;</p>\r\n ', '2022-02-18 04:58:07'),
