(112, 331, 229, '<p>Prototype 1 is sorters.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prototype 2 is a cleaner</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prototype 4 is a compactor</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Variation 1&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I did not have any problems with the overall design of the machine. I did have a problem with prototype 2(cleaner). It was in a rectangle prism shape so it would prevent the plastics from being cleaned properly. I also had a problem with the way it was using the pressure washer. It was going up and down using a motor and a gear rack which had two problems. Problem was that it would be slow. Problem two is it is unnecessary because the nozzle of the pressure washer would already cover a wide range. So it would increase the cost for no reason. I also have a problem with prototype 1(sorter). Even the best object recognization software struggle with recognizing the object if it is dirtied up. So the problem would be it wouldn&#39;t be able to sort them properly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Variation 2</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A problem I still had was that not only the plastic, glass, and metals were being sent to the trashcan/ compactor some of the other stuff was still being sent. Another problem I had was that after getting the wet paper is useless for recycling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Variation 1</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To address the problem with prototype 2 I would change the shape of it to be a cylinder that way everything is cleaned properly. To address the pressure washer problem I would take out the mechanism that makes it go up and down and instead put in 5 different pressure washers instead of 3. I would do this so that way it would clean all the sides and not just 3 sides of the container. To address the problem with the object recognization software not recognizing it I would change the way it was sorted in the first place. How the sorting would work now is. First, the trash you threw would be at the top of the machine. Then, it will allow 2-3 pieces of trash to be lowered onto a conveyor belt. On the conveyor belt, there will be a camera using R-FCN(Region-based Fully Convolutional Network) which is an object recognition algorithm to sense what the trash is. For this stage, it will sort between group 1(plastic, glass, metal) and everything else but it will use a 40% match rate to sort instead of the default 95%. This stage is mainly done to reduce the amount of trash getting into the washer. So a 40% match rate is done because object recognition software struggles to identify the object unless it is clean. So a 40% match rate will allow it to reduce the amount of trash in the cleaner and still have all of group 1 be sent to the there compactors except for glass which will sit in a normal bin.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Variation 2</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To fix that problem I added an extra cleaning process for the plastic and the metal before it reaches the compactors. I took at the paper portion of the machine.</p>\r\n ', '', '2022-02-12 03:46:06'),
