(326, 241, '<p>Lunch ladies have to direct 5 people in the lunchroom. The lunch ladies won&rsquo;t have to direct people in. They use a person to do that as a job. To tell the students how many can come in</p>\r\n', '<p>The result I&#39;m looking for is the people that work the doors will have different things they can do and they won&rsquo;t have to yell at the students and the students won&rsquo;t have to get yelled at about that any more.</p>\r\n', '<p>I can make a machine that says how many people can come in. There will be two, one on one side and the other on the exit door counting how many people go out. I can also just make a stick that blocks the door and has a remote so the lunch ladies can open and close it when needed to let people in. I decided to do the first one because it&#39;s more convenient, and has more good features added to it.</p>\r\n', '2022-01-17 00:06:46'),
(324, 242, '<p><strong>The problem that we&nbsp; are trying to solve is how to prevent glasses from fogging up due to the temperature falling below the&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; dew&nbsp; point, moisture in the air condenses, changes from vapor to a liquid, and causes fogging. To put it simply we&#39;re trying to make a thing that will stop the glasses from fogging. We came up with this idea because we both wear glasses and wearing the glasses with the mask. It always causes the glasses to fog up.</strong></p>\r\n', '<p><strong>The result that we&#39;re trying to achieve is no longer having your glasses fog up due to the difference in moisture</strong></p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Some possible solutions are antifog lens, Wash glasses with soap and water and antifog wipes and spray. I choose to pursue the antifog wipes and spray. I decided to pick the spray and wipes because they seem to be the most convenient for people to use and convenient to make. It did not require anybody to modify their glasses or anything, it was simple and easy anybody can use it. That&#39;s how we came up with the solution.</strong></p>\r\n', '2022-01-17 00:47:43'),
(330, 227, '<p>The problem I want to solve is foggy glasses when wearing a mask. I have this problem because I&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; wear glasses and a mask all the time and my glasses fog up a lot, which obviously disturbs my ability to see.</p>\r\n', '<p>The result I want is something that works effectively to prevent glasses from fogging, but it has to be something small and cheap so you can keep it in your pocket, like a wipe.</p>\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Some possible solutions are using anti fogging spray, anti fogging lenses, adjusting your glasses, and anti fogging wipes. I chose to pursue the anti fogging wipes because it is something cheap and compact, it also hasn&rsquo;t been done before. If the wipe is soaked with a soapy solution, theroricticly the wipe should work like the anti fogging spray. We could also soak the wipe in anti fogging spray.</p>\r\n', '2022-01-17 01:11:36'),
