(331, 229, '<p>The problem I&#39;m trying to solve is the contamination in recycables&nbsp;renders them useless for recycling. I originally wanted to do something to make recycling being more of a public relations stunt then an actual soulotion to climit change. But I relized then relized the actual problem is how recycling is not effiecient. As i was doing reasearch into the problem I stumbled onto contamination in recycables and I relized that this was a bigger problem and chose to pursue it instead of the system being inefficeient.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>I want to have a michine that will reduce contamination. There is many different ways to reduce the contaminations. The main three are food remains, trash going in recylables, and liquids being left in the containers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>One possible solution to solve 2 of the main problems(Food remains and liquid remains) is a high-pressure water nozzle that will clean the inside of plastics. The water will be at high pressure so that way it can clean all the food grease and leftover liquids out. &nbsp;There can be multiple nozzles that can be connected to one water source. Another solution can also be a rotating brush that goes into the plastic bottle/recyclable which shoots high-pressure water out of it to get the same result, clean all the food grease and the leftover food remains. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To solve non-recyclables being sent with recyclables I thought of an app that will scan the barcode of the item read the label and say if it is recyclable in your area or not. I also thought of the same sort of idea but instead of it being on an app it would be on the public trashcans and indicate if it is recyclable or not. It would also compress on itself to make more room.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A solution to solve the food remains is to have a container where you can clean your food waste. Then rinse it with water and throw it away.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A solution that solves all the main problems is a machine in which you would first throw all of your trash in. Then it would sort your trash into 5 categories glass, paper, plastic, metal, and trash. Before the glass and the plastics reached their bin they would go through a washing cycle. After the washing cycle, it will reach their bin. Then the bins for the trash, plastics, and paper will compress on themselves to make more room.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe solution I decided to pursue was the last one. I wanted to solve all the main three problems so I tried to incorporate my earlier ideas into one machine. That is how I came up with that machine.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2022-02-01 06:33:23'),
