 if it is recyclable or not. It would also compress on itself to make more room.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5:</strong>&nbsp;A solution to solve the food remains is to have a container where you can clean your food waste. Then rinse it with water and throw it away.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6:</strong>&nbsp;A solution to compress the items is a 2-axis compressor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7</strong>: A solution to compressing it I thought of a machine that would melt the plastics down into more compact shapes so it&#39;s easier to transport.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>8:</strong>&nbsp;A solution to compress the plastic water bottles is a machine that would suck all the air out of the plastic.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>9:</strong>&nbsp;A solution that solves all the main problems is a machine in which you would first throw all of your trash. Then it would sort your trash into 5 categories glass, paper, plastic, metal, and trash. Before the glass and the plastics reached their bin they would go through a washing cycle. After the washing cycle, it will reach their bin. Then the bins for the trash, plastics, and paper will compress themselves to make more room.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The solution I decided to pursue was the last one. I wanted to solve all the main three problems so I tried to incorporate my earlier ideas into one machine. That is how I came up with that machine and that&#39;s why I chose to pursue it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2022-05-12 03:16:55');
