(139, 331, 229, '<p>The first type of reasearch I did was look through the internet to find smart recycling bins. I searched on home depot and other appliance websites.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>The second type of reasearch I did was call the local recycling center in ann arbor. I asked them about different things that the user can do to help reduce contamination and make recycling more efficient. I also asked them if any devices can help the user in those processes. To which they responded with a few answers.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>The third type of research I did was talking to my mentors and family about the possibility of the invention working and its usefulness. My mentors said that my invention is useful, but it has a few problems in fitting into the existing recycling ecosystem. My family said it was a useful invention, but making it profitable would be the problem.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>The fourth type of research I did was just more online research on how users can reduce the amount of contamination that gets into recycling plants. I went through a lot of different government websites. I also looked at different existing products the help deal with this.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>I found a few similar inventions. The first type is more of a category than a single invention but automatic bottle cleaners. My invention uses similar technology as the bottle cleaners but they don&#39;t only clean bottles but all different recyclables The second thing I found where different types of recycling organizers which only help you organize the different recyclables into different categories. Which are useless since we have a single stream system in the United States. I looked up different smart trashcans. I found one main real competitor in the market they are called Bin-e Smart Waste(https://www.bine.world). The thing my invention will do better is clean the recyclables and also serve a bigger market. Since their invention is used mainly in offices while mine will be in apartment complexes, dorms, and other types of community complexes. &nbsp; There was another idea but it never went into the market it was by Cambridge University. All theirs did was sort different types of beverage containers. Mine sorts more types of recyclables and mine also cleans them.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2022-02-07 00:17:35'),
